<seg id=1> Ding Hao Becomes The First Disabled College Student Who Has Grown Up in An Orphanage </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Hangzhou, September 1st, (Xinhua News Agency) Orphanized since childhood and growing up at an orphanage in Hangzhou, Ding Hao received his admission offer days ago from Hang Zhou University to become a student in the Philosophy and Sociology Department. </seg>
<seg id=3> It is said that Ding, 19 this year, is the first disabled orphan college student who has grown up at an orphanage in new China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> "On receiving the offer, I had the impetus to jump up", Ding said, but he could not jump, of course, to express his excitement. </seg>
<seg id=5> A victim of polio, a high fever crippled him when he was 3 years old. The same year he was adopted by an orphanage. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Ding finished primary school at the orphanage and then attended a middle school at a neighboring town. </seg>
<seg id=7> At the beginning, teachers of the orphanage accompanied him to school and picked him up, but from the second year, he became a resident student and went back to the orphanage only for weekends. He never missed a class, rain or shine. </seg>
<seg id=8> This year, he joined in the college entrance examination, and was admitted by Hangzhou University. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Ding owes his success to people from all walks of life in society. </seg>
<seg id=10> The orphanage took considerate care of him in all the 16 years after he was adopted. Since last year, the orphanage paid over 3000 yuan for his tuition, books and nutriment. </seg>
<seg id=11> Help has been offered from others as well. </seg>
<seg id=12> After Knowing that Ding was admitted to college, Hangzhou Changlong Food & Oil Trading Company donated 20,000 yuan to help him, An artificial limb factory gave him an wheelchair and walk sticks. </seg>
</p>
